def model_select(num_states, time_indice, log_returns = log_returns, date_str = date_str):
    # There are totally 252 - 67 + 1 = 186 samples.
    # So index is from 0 + 67 to 185 + 67 = 252.
    for index in time_indice:
        if type(index) != int or index < 67 or index > 252:
            raise Exception("Index is wrong. It should be an integer between [0, 185]!")

    date_str = date_str[1:]
    results = {}
    for index in time_indice:
        all_return = log_returns[pd.Series(log_returns.index, index = log_returns.index).apply(lambda x: x[5:10] in date_str[index - 24: index]).values]
        prev_return, cur_return = all_return[:-390], all_return[-390:]
        cur_date = cur_return.index[0][0:10]

        # models = []
        lnL, aic, bic = [], [], []
        for num_state in range(2, num_states + 1):
            # try large "n_iter" and different "random state" will improve the accuracy of the algorithm a lot!
            model = HMM(n_components=num_state, random_state=343).fit(prev_return.values.reshape(-1, 1))

            if not model.monitor_.converged:
                raise Exception("Did not converge, please check!")

            # Store models
            # models.append(model)

            # Determine the number of estimated parameters k
            # Ref - "https://machinelearninginterview.com/topics/machine-learning/latexpage-how-many-parameters-are-there-for-an-hmm-model-given-below-px-ypxypyprod_t1tpx_ty_tpy_ty_t-1/"
            # initial node prob + emission matrix of Gaussian + transition matrix
            # k = num_state * (1 + prev_return.shape[0] + num_state)
            # But in general, the coefficients in emission matrix and initial node prob are generated by the distribution parameters.
            # According to the number of free scalar parameters in this algorithm
            k = num_state * (num_state + 2) - 1

            lnL.append(model.score(prev_return.values.reshape(-1, 1)))
            aic.append(- 2 * lnL[-1] + 2 * k)
            bic.append(- 2 * lnL[-1] + np.log(prev_return.shape[0]) * k)

        results[cur_date] = pd.DataFrame({"LL": lnL, "AIC": aic, "BIC": bic}, index = list([i for i in range(2, num_states + 1)]))
        print(cur_date + " Done!")
    return results

def plot_model_select(df, analyze_num):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(20, 12));
    plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.02);

    n = len(model_select_plot_df)
    for i, (cur_date, results) in enumerate(df.items()):
        ax1 = fig.add_subplot(n, 2, 2 * i + 1);
        ax1.plot(results.index, results["AIC"], label = "AIC");
        ax1.plot(results.index, results["BIC"], label = "BIC\n" + "Date: " + cur_date);
        ylim = ax1.get_ylim()
        ax1.scatter(analyze_num, results.loc[analyze_num, "BIC"], zorder=2, color="k")
        ax1.plot([analyze_num] * 200, np.linspace(ylim[0], results.loc[analyze_num, "BIC"], 200), linestyle = "--", color = "k", zorder=2)
        ax1.set_ylim(ylim[0], ylim[1])
        plt.legend(loc="upper left")
        plt.grid()
        if i == n - 1:
            plt.xlabel("Number of states")

        ax2 = fig.add_subplot(n, 2, 2 * i + 2);
        ax2.plot(results.index, results["LL"], label = "Log likelihood\n" + "Date: " + cur_date);
        ylim = ax2.get_ylim()
        ax2.scatter(analyze_num, results.loc[analyze_num, "LL"], zorder=2, color="k")
        ax2.plot([analyze_num] * 200, np.linspace(ylim[0], results.loc[analyze_num, "LL"], 200), linestyle = "--", color = "k", zorder=2)
        ax2.set_ylim(ylim[0], ylim[1])
        plt.legend(loc="lower left")
        plt.grid()
        if i == n - 1:
            plt.xlabel("Number of states")

def gen_norm_pdf(hmm_model, range_std = 3):
    mean_vec = hmm_model.means_.flatten()
    sigma_vec = np.sqrt(hmm_model.covars_.flatten())
    lo_vec = mean_vec - range_std * sigma_vec
    up_vec = mean_vec + range_std * sigma_vec
    x_vec = np.linspace(lo_vec.min(), up_vec.max(), int(1e5))
    y_vecs = []
    for i in range(mean_vec.shape[0]):
        curr_dist = norm(mean_vec[i], sigma_vec[i])
        y_vecs.append(curr_dist.pdf(x_vec))
    return np.array(x_vec), np.array(y_vecs), mean_vec, sigma_vec

def plot_HMM_forecast(num_states, time_indice, control_vec, log_returns = log_returns, date_str = date_str):
    # There are totally 252 - 67 + 1 = 186 samples.
    # So index is from 0 + 67 to 185 + 67 = 252.
    for index in time_indice:
        if type(index) != int or index < 67 or index > 252:
            raise Exception("Index is wrong. It should be an integer between [0, 185]!")

    date_str = date_str[1:]

    for j, index in enumerate(time_indice):
        all_return = log_returns[pd.Series(log_returns.index, index = log_returns.index).apply(lambda x: x[5:10] in date_str[index - 24: index]).values]
        prev_return, cur_return = all_return[:-390], all_return[-390:]
        cur_date = cur_return.index[0][0:10]

        model = HMM(n_components=num_states, random_state=343).fit(prev_return.values.reshape(-1, 1))

        if not model.monitor_.converged:
                raise Exception("Did not converge, please check!")

        # use the Viterbi algorithm to predict the most likely sequence of states given the model
        states = model.predict(cur_return.values.reshape(-1, 1))
        prop_per_state = model.predict_proba(cur_return.values.reshape(-1, 1)).mean(axis=0)

        fig = plt.figure(figsize=(20, 12));
        plt.subplots_adjust(wspace=0);

        control_l, control_u = control_vec[j]
        # plot model states over time
        ax1 = plt.subplot2grid((1, 3), (0, 0), colspan = 1);
        x_vec, y_vecs, mean_vec, sigma_vec = gen_norm_pdf(model, range_std = 0.5)
        for i in range(model.n_components):
            ax1.plot(y_vecs[i], x_vec, label = "State%d\nMean: %.4e; Std: %.4e\nProportion of time: %.4f" % (i, mean_vec[i], sigma_vec[i], prop_per_state[i]));
        ax1.set_xlim(int(y_vecs.max() + 10), -10);
        ax1.set_ylim(control_l, control_u);
        ax1.set_title("Emission Gaussian distributions", fontsize=18);
        plt.xticks(fontsize=18);
        plt.yticks(fontsize=18);
        plt.legend(fontsize=14, loc="upper left");
        plt.xlabel("Probability density function", fontsize=18);

        plot_num = cur_return.shape[0]
        ax2 = plt.subplot2grid((1, 3), (0, 1), colspan=2);
        for i in range(model.n_components):
            index = (states[:plot_num] == i)
            ax2.plot(np.where(index)[0], cur_return[index].values,
                     ".", ms=15, mfc="k", label = "State%d Observations\nTotal: %d" % (i, np.where(index)[0].shape[0]), alpha=0.7, zorder=2);
        ax2.plot(cur_return.values[:plot_num], lw=1.5, alpha=0.7, zorder=1, label = "Log Returns at\n" + "      " + cur_date);

        ax2.set_xlim(-int(plot_num/80), plot_num + int(plot_num/80));
        ax2.set_ylim(control_l, control_u);
        ax2.tick_params(labelleft=False, left=False, labelright=True, right=True);
        ax2.set_xlabel("Time index", fontsize=18);
        ax2.set_title("Log Returns and their underlying states (Viterbi algorithm)", fontsize=18);
        plt.xticks(fontsize=18);
        plt.yticks(fontsize=18);
        plt.legend(fontsize=14, loc="upper right");

In [ ]:
def get_emission(x , dists):
    res = []
    for dist in dists:
        res.append(dist.pdf(x))
    return np.array(res)
In [ ]:
def sum_adjust(df):
    return df / df.sum()
In [ ]:
def omega_induction(previous, transmat):
    res = []
    for i in range(previous.shape[0]):
        value = 0
        for j in range(previous.shape[0]):
            # transmat[j,i] means the probability from state j to state i.
            value += transmat[j,i] * previous[str(j)]
        res.append(value)
    return np.array(res)

def HMM_forecast(num_states, index, log_returns = log_returns, date_str = date_str):
    # There are totally 252 - 67 + 1 = 186 samples.
    # So index is from 0 + 67 to 185 + 67 = 252.
    if type(index) != int or index < 67 or index > 252:
        raise Exception("Index is wrong. It should be an integer between [67, 252]!")

    date_str = date_str[1:]
    all_return = log_returns[pd.Series(log_returns.index, index = log_returns.index).apply(lambda x: x[5:10] in date_str[index - 24: index]).values]
    prev_return, cur_return = all_return[:-390], all_return[-391:-1]
    cur_date = cur_return.index[1][0:10]

    model = HMM(n_components=num_states, random_state=343).fit(prev_return.values.reshape(-1, 1))
    if not model.monitor_.converged:
        raise Exception("Did not converge, please check!")

    gaussian_dists = []
    for i in range(3):
        gaussian_dists.append(norm(model.means_.flatten()[i], np.sqrt(model.covars_.flatten())[i]))

    col_names = [str(i) for i in range(num_states)]
    temp_index = [0]
    for i in range(1, 390):
        temp_index = temp_index + [i, i]
    left_index = temp_index + [390]
    right_index = [0] + temp_index
    omega = pd.DataFrame([], columns = col_names, index = [str(i) + "_" + str(j) for i, j in zip(left_index, right_index)])

    # Initialization
    omega.loc["0_0", :] = model.startprob_
    omega.loc["0_0", :] = omega.loc["0_0", :] * get_emission(cur_return[0], gaussian_dists)
    omega.loc["0_0", :] = sum_adjust(omega.loc["0_0", :])

    # Induction
    for i in range(1, 390):
        omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i-1), :] = omega_induction(omega.loc[str(i-1) + "_" + str(i-1), :], model.transmat_)
        omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i), :] = omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i-1), :]
        omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i), :] = omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i), :] * get_emission(cur_return[i], gaussian_dists)
        omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i), :] = sum_adjust(omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i), :])

    # Termination
    omega.loc["390_389", :] = omega_induction(omega.loc["389_389", :], model.transmat_)

    # Forecast
    forecast_return = []
    for i in range(1, 391):
        forecast_return.append((model.means_.flatten() * omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i-1), :].values).sum())

    return pd.DataFrame(forecast_return, index = all_return[-390:].index)

def IOHMM_forecast(num_states, bucket_num, index, signals, log_returns = log_returns, date_str = date_str):
    # There are totally 252 - 90 + 1 = 163 samples.
    # So index is from 0 + 90 to 185 + 67 = 252.
    if type(index) != int or index < 90 or index > 252:
        raise Exception("Index is wrong. It should be an integer between [90, 252]!")

    date_str = date_str[1:]
    all_return = log_returns[pd.Series(log_returns.index, index = log_returns.index).apply(lambda x: x[5:10] in date_str[index - 24: index]).values]
    prev_return, cur_return = all_return[:-390], all_return[-391:-1]
    cur_date = cur_return.index[1][0:10]

    sign_temp = signals[prev_return.index[0]: prev_return.index[-1]]
    sign_cur = signals[cur_return.index[0]: cur_return.index[-1]]

    # split training data
    new_data = []
    thre = np.quantile(sign_temp, np.linspace(0, 1, bucket_num + 1))[1:-1]
    new_data.append(sign_temp[sign_temp < thre[0]].dropna())
    for i in range(bucket_num - 2):
        new_data.append(sign_temp[(thre[i] <= sign_temp) & (sign_temp < thre[i+1])].dropna())
    new_data.append(sign_temp[thre[bucket_num - 2] <= sign_temp].dropna())

    # train models
    models = []
    for data in new_data:
        model = HMM(n_components=num_states, random_state=343).fit(data.values.reshape(-1, 1))
        if not model.monitor_.converged:
            raise Exception("Did not converge, please check!")
        models.append(model)

    model_means = [model.means_.flatten() for model in models]
    model_stds = [np.sqrt(model.covars_.flatten()) for model in models]
    model_trans = [model.transmat_ for model in models]
    orders = [np.argsort(model_std) for model_std in model_stds]

    # get model information
    model_means = [mean[order] for order, mean in zip(orders, model_means)]
    model_stds = [std[order] for order, std in zip(orders, model_stds)]
    model_trans = [tran[order, :][:, order] for order, tran in zip(orders, model_trans)]

    gaussian_dists_vec = []
    for mean, std in zip(model_means, model_stds):
        gaussian_dists = []
        for i in range(num_states):
            gaussian_dists.append(norm(mean[i], std[i]))
        gaussian_dists_vec.append(gaussian_dists)

    # get test date index
    sign_index = np.array([0] * 390)
    for t in thre:
        sign_index += (sign_cur > t).astype(int).values.flatten()
    sign_index = pd.DataFrame(sign_index, sign_cur.index)[0]

    # the following is similar to HMM
    col_names = [str(i) for i in range(num_states)]
    temp_index = [0]
    for i in range(1, 390):
        temp_index = temp_index + [i, i]
    left_index = temp_index + [390]
    right_index = [0] + temp_index
    omega = pd.DataFrame([], columns = col_names, index = [str(i) + "_" + str(j) for i, j in zip(left_index, right_index)])

    # Initialization
    omega.loc["0_0", :] = model.startprob_
    omega.loc["0_0", :] = omega.loc["0_0", :] * get_emission(cur_return[0], gaussian_dists_vec[sign_index[0]])
    omega.loc["0_0", :] = sum_adjust(omega.loc["0_0", :])

    # Induction
    for i in range(1, 390):
        omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i-1), :] = omega_induction(omega.loc[str(i-1) + "_" + str(i-1), :], model_trans[sign_index[i-1]])
        omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i), :] = omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i-1), :]
        omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i), :] = omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i), :] * get_emission(cur_return[i], gaussian_dists_vec[sign_index[i]])
        omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i), :] = sum_adjust(omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i), :])

    # Termination
    omega.loc["390_389", :] = omega_induction(omega.loc["389_389", :], model_trans[sign_index[389]])

    # Forecast
    forecast_return = []
    for i in range(1, 391):
        forecast_return.append((model_means[sign_index[i-1]] * omega.loc[str(i) + "_" + str(i-1), :].values).sum())

    return pd.DataFrame(forecast_return, index = all_return[-390:].index), model_means, model_stds, model_trans

def convert_signal_IOHMM(df, signal_coef = signal_coef):
    signal_coef = signal_coef[23:]
    temp_df = df.copy()
    for i in range(signal_coef.index.shape[0]):
        index = pd.Series(temp_df.index, index = temp_df.index).apply(lambda x: x[0:10] == signal_coef.index[i]).values
        temp_df.loc[index] = (temp_df.loc[index] - signal_coef["mean"][i]) / signal_coef["std"][i]
    temp_df[temp_df > 1], temp_df[temp_df < -1] = 1, -1
    return temp_df
